Android Studio change cache folder, but C:\Users\Administrator\.AndroidStudio3.1 created automatically
1. change .AndroidStudio: D:\Program Files\Android\Android Studio\bin\idea.properties
    idea.config.path=E:/Android/ideaconfig/.AndroidStudio/config
    idea.system.path=E:/Android/ideaconfig/.AndroidStudio/system
    #from C:\Users\Administrator\.AndroidStudio3.1  (3.1 is current version, others can deleted)
 2. add system enviornment to change .gradle
    GRADLE_USER_HOME=E:/Android/ideaconfig/.gradle
    #(or) Settings -> Gradle -> Service directory path: E:/Android/ideaconfig/.gradle
 3. add system enviornment and modify xx.ini path to change .android
    # config avd path under sdk home (from: C:\Users\Administrator)
    ANDROID_SDK_HOME=E:\Android\Sdk
    #(modify) path=E:\Android\Sdk\.android\avd\Nexus_5X_API_25_x86.avd

